# Augment Guidelines for Hostel Booking System

## Agent Mode Configuration
- ALWAYS operate in agent mode for automatic file editing
- Enable direct file manipulation without manual intervention
- Use tools: edit, create, read, search, replace, command

## Go Development
- Follow Go idioms and best practices
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add comments for exported functions
- Use error handling pattern: if err != nil
- Prefer table-driven tests
- Use gofumpt and goimports for formatting

## Project Structure
- Backend code in /backend directory
- Frontend code in /frontend/svetu directory
- Database migrations in /backend/migrations
- API handlers in /backend/internal/proj/
- Swagger docs in /backend/docs/

## Code Style
- Use gofumpt for Go formatting
- Use Prettier for TypeScript/JavaScript
- Follow existing patterns in the codebase
- Maintain consistency with project conventions


## Frontend Development
- Use DaisyUI classes for UI components
- Utilize Redux Toolkit for state management (not Zustand)
- Run yarn format && yarn lint && yarn build before finishing
- Follow React 19 and Next.js 15 best practices

## Backend Development
- Run make format && make lint before finishing
- Update swagger docs with make generate-types when API changes
- Follow Fiber framework conventions
- Use proper error handling with translated placeholders
